 my whole set. <br><br>If not for the quest I do not know if I would have had a purpose in those levels besides level and kill level and kill. <p><I><B>Gilfalas Elaandrin</I></B><br>Guildmaster of Twilight Order<br>Koada'Vie, Defender of Felwithe and Knight of Truth<br>Cavalier of the 52nd<br>Bertoxxulous Server</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~pfichera/_images/TO.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 3/16/01 1:09:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadmandelu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adman Delu</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.spree.com/sip/tspaar/noel/fantasy/flame.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 514<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/01 9:48:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/nycdamian/eb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> You should do Ro for several reasons. Here's two.<br><br>Faction. <br>You need to do the faction work with the various paladin guilds for various reasons. Deepwater faction (bracers) will get you Fiery Avenger, Defender. Qeynos faction will get you Soulfire. <br><br>Look.<br>Rygorr not only looks like chain, it makes you look like a fruitcake, especially on humans. The pants look like you're wearing panties on the outside for gawd sake. Ro looks like steel, what a paladin should be flaunting. <br><br>Nuff said. <p><a href=http://members.aol.com/nycdamian/stats.jpg height=700 width=800><img src=http://members.aol.com/nycdamian/Montage4.jpg height=100 width=350></a><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="mailto:damianicus@hotmail.com">Adman</A> 53 pal, Morrissey 32 brd, Derran 48 rng, Malabu 37 dru, etc...</FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uranadorvalorblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranador Valorblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/01 1:03:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> Ro Armor is NEVER a waste of time and it also gives you a good sense of accomplishment when you complete it. At 27, there is no other comparable armor easily available unless you have a large amount of money available to you.<br><br>You do not need to have any skill in smithing, but I would put at least 1 point into it just because.<br><br>And I agree with Gilfalas. The Ro quests take you all over the original continents of Norrath to obtain the components for ronium and the components for the molds. Be patient, be persistent. I was told by many people that I should just give up. I am glad that I didn't. I get many compliments from people on how it looks and it makes me feel proud to wear it. It is very good questing experience.<br><br>I would say that you should make sure all of your factions are where they should be first before actually trying to get all of the pieces. Read the Tomes of Knowledge section on this message board to find out how to get your factions where they need to be.<br><br>For me, the hardest piece to get was the vambraces. You have to camp the plague shark in Erud's Crossing which is a 2 hour spawn and he doesn't drop the rotten shark portions every time.<br><br>Good luck to you on your quest. It is well worth the time.<br> <p>Ranador Valorblade<BR>Level 39 Paladin<BR>Knight of Truth<BR>Imperatores Sortium<BR>Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulumaden69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lumaden69</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/01 1:20:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> Do the Ro armor quests mate, for smithing i put 5 training points just to be safe /shrug call it paranoia<br>the Resists off the Legs, BP, and 2 bracers comes very handy when you get to dragon killing status :) <br>Rygor armor is FUGLY imho on a high elf you look like a fairy noob egyptian wanna be lol <br>ALSO the molds you get regardless i have found there is a necro in paineel noobie section beside guards (before the hill to go to the hole) kill this degenerate to raise DW faction for the bracer its easy and it should be green at your level<br><br>Do the quests you will lose your mind how much exp you get at getting the molds!! at level 31 half a yellow bub!! this is great to make up for the time to waddle around norrath colecting the items<br> <br><br>Thurgardin Armor is nice off the dorfs yes if you go and are lucky to find some rotting its very good and looks nice (hang around the section and some high level dorf killers might feel generous)<br><br>This is off topic but i might as well post it here there are 3 armor set quests with the introduction of SoV<br> Thurg, Kael, and Skyshrine the quests are basicly the same but factions come into play the best armor is from Giants in Kael Drakkel, second is Skyshrine, followed by Thurg dorfs<br><br>My faction is KOS to giants and warmly to dorfs this i am going to change in the next 2 weeks the Kael armor is outstanding AC and for stats the SS armor kicks ass <p><center><FONT color="56A9D1">Lumaden Dragonrider</FONT></center><br><center>52 Cavalier</center><br><center><FONT color="A33E6A">Officer ~~Vis Veres~~</FONT></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uekimemsti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ekimemsti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/01 7:17:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> Thank you all for your comments and time.<br>I have decided to get the armor.  Guess<br>I'll start working on my faction now  :-P<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uloven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/01 6:35:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> I agree...do the Ro armor quests...you also might want to buy some Fine Plate armor from a smith and use that until you have Ro armor. <p>Loven Laviedemer <BR>Lvl 51 Deepwater Knight <BR>Ethos <BR>Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzuchrom69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zuchrom69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/01 6:49:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.clipartcastle.com/anim3/smoke.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> Unlike the others I say don't waste the 5 weeks it will take to do this silver-looking Ivy.  The time it will take you to raise each and every faction, the insane price of making the runium bars, the rarity of sands of ro, and not to mention the rarity and difficutly of every piece you need to make each mold, make banded worth wearing til lvl 46, when you can hit the planes.  Buy bronze, steel, raw silk...ANYTHING but Ro.  Making My Ro was the biggest series of mistakes I have ever made.  Ivy (surprise, rangers get same/better gear as usual), is at MOST 2 ac lower, with MUCH better plus to stats.  Save your pp, and buy real armour.  You're looking at a paladin who was in full bronze til 41.  Ghetto looking, but just as effective, believe me.<br><br> <p>Zuchrom Freehaven,<br>   the Force of Freedom.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaldaasdei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldaas DeI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/01 6:57:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kaldaasdei.tripod.com/Kaldaas45.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> I disagree with Zuchrom and Hareq so much it's not even funny. The resists on Ro are great for raids. The AC is great, only Fine Plate comes close, and if you're wearing Fine Plate/Bronze/Raw Silk/Banded until 46, you're... words escape me. As others have mentioned the factions involved are used for bigger quests too, like the FA/FD. <br><br>You can begin the quests at 27. You can do most parts in a group (fairy dust, maybe Mistmoore, but I wouldn't go to MM till 30), and you can start building faction in 30. 30 is a loooong level, so you might as well make the most of it. Also, lots of higher level Paladins are more than willing to pass on a few components to you, as they know how hard it is to do the quests. <br><br>Ro Armour <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> worthwhile. <p>Kaldaas<br>46th Paladin<br>Divide et Impera<br>Bristlebane Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uekimemsti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ekimemsti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/01 7:56:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2865.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/ekimemstiestervon/c_paladin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro Armor and smithing...</span><hr size=1> Yea... I'm very big on getting my faction up now<br>for my epic, and I want the resistants with the ro.<br>Only problem im going to have is affording the<br>enchanted plat bars... I have 250pp in the bank<br>now (spent a bit getting my smithing to master).<br>I have 4 sands of ro (from kind high levels that<br>didnt need it)  Guess I'm going to take a break<br>and fight some mobs and try to make some 